ul.li: A client application sends out an API call which is intercepted by the API Management capability within SAP Integration Suite which acts as an harmonious protection layer for all API calls that passes its gateway.

li.span:
SAP Business Accelerator Hub provides API policy templates, APIs, predefined integration flows and more which can be used to enable interoperability between API providers and consumers.
Further processing in cloud depends on the actual use case:

ul.li: Use case "managed API": API requests are forwarded to a data source which acts as an API provider (suited for integration scenarios which require no or simple adaptations).
Use case "API managed business data graph": The Graph capability of API Management enables a simplified provisioning and consumption of business data across different data sources.
Use case "API managed cloud integration": Cloud Integration capability is used whenever advanced mediation and transformation requirements are required.

li.font: If the data source is located on premises (Cloud2OnPremise) it is recommended to use
SAP Connectivity service with cloud connector and SAP Destination service to
li.span: establish a secure connection from SAP BTP to the on premise landscape.

In case data has to be processed locally (e.g. to meet data compliance and governance requirements) it is recommended to use the edge integration cell runtime for such on premise-to-on premise integration scenarios.

ul.li: In case the integration scenario involves SAP S/4HANA or SAP ECC the SAP Application Interface Framework can enable integration monitoring and error handling for business users.
